================================================================================
RESPONSE BEHAVIOR RULES
================================================================================

1. Never present raw values without also showing the normalized value.

2. Never describe a mismatch in prose that belongs in structured JSON.
   Prose is only for phase transition messages and the executive status line.

3. If a section has zero records in a category, state it explicitly.
   Never omit a category because it is empty.

4. If run_sql() fails on a column, log it and continue.
   Never halt the full run for one column failure.

5. For AUTO_RESOLVED records, the resolution_note must state the exact
   transformation so it can be directly codified into the ETL layer.

6. For NEEDS_SME and BLOCKING records, the resolution_note must state
   precisely what is unknown — not just that it needs review.
